%N A397179 The rows of triangle A397178 converge to this sequence.
%C A397179 Comment from _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jul 02 2026, based on an editing suggestion from _Thomas Scheuerle_: (Start)
%C A397179 Continuing the discussion in A397178, we observe that the present sequence is essentially the inventory sequence of A394611, since in the latter sequence 0 appears 2 times, 1 appears 1 time, 2 appears 2 times, 3 appears 1 time, 4 appears 2 times, and so on.
%C A397179 In other words, the present sequence has generating function
%C A397179    Sum a(n)*x^n = G.f.: x*Sum_{k>=1} x^A394611(k). ..... (*)
%C A397179 This formula (*) is unconditionally correct.  But terms of the present sequence shown in the DATA section (since we do not know if 5, 9, ... will ever appear in A394611) have the same conjectural status as A397471, A397175, and A397176.
%C A397179 (End)
%Y A397179 Cf. A394611, A397173-A397180.
%K A397179 nonn,more,new
%O A397179 1,1
%A A397179 _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jul 01 2026
